.TH SYSTEM-UPDATE-INHIBITOR 8 "March 2026" "system-update-inhibitor" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
system-update-inhibitor \- systemd shutdown inhibitor daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B system-update-inhibitor
.RI [ \-c " config_path" ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B system-update-inhibitor
runs as a daemon and registers a delay inhibitor lock with
.BR systemd-logind (8).
When logind emits
.B PrepareForShutdown
on D-Bus, the daemon executes the configured shutdown script or binary,
waits for it to exit, and then releases the inhibitor lock.
.PP
This allows system update workflows and other pre-shutdown tasks to run
before poweroff or reboot continues.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config " "PATH"
Path to configuration file.
If omitted,
.I /etc/system-update-inhibitor.conf
is used.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is read from:
.TP
.I /etc/system-update-inhibitor.conf
Supported keys include:
.TP
.B shutdown_script
Absolute path to the executable to run on shutdown.
.TP
.B shutdown_script_user
Optional user name or numeric UID to run the script as.
.TP
.B shutdown_script_group
Optional group name or numeric GID to run the script as.
.TP
.B shutdown_script_env
Optional environment file with one
.I KEY=VALUE
entry per line.
.TP
.B set_max_inhibit_delay
Boolean. If true, enforce
.B InhibitDelayMaxSec
in logind.conf.
.TP
.B restart_logind_after_set
Boolean. If true, restart logind after updating its config.
.TP
.B max_inhibit_delay
Desired
.B InhibitDelayMaxSec
value in seconds.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/system-update-inhibitor.conf
Primary configuration file.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/systemd/system/system-update-inhibitor.service
Systemd service unit file.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR systemd-logind (8),
.BR logind.conf (5),
.BR systemctl (1)